Package abstractDataTypesPackage

Interface GraphADT<T>

Type Parameters:
T - Generic type
All Known Implementing Classes:
IntegerUndirectedAdjacencyListIndexedGraph, PersonUndirectedAdjacencyListIndexedGraph
public interface GraphADT<T>
Interface of the Graph abstract data type. This interface hold the basic methods that must be implemented.
Author:
Borja Moralejo Tobajas

      Tries to add the element to the graph.
      Parameters:
      element - - Element to add.
      Returns:
      boolean - returns true if it was added, false otherwise.

    • removeVertex

      boolean removeVertex​(T element)
      Tries to remove the element from the graph.
      Parameters:
      element - - Element to remove, doesn't need to be in the graph, if it's not in the graph it will return false.
      Returns:
      boolean - return true if the element was removed, false otherwise.

    • addEdge

      boolean addEdge​(T element1, T element2)
      Tries to create an edge between element1 and element2. If one or both of the elements aren't in the graph, it will return false.
      Parameters:
      element1 - - Element to create an edge from.
      element2 - - Element to create an edge to.
      Returns:
      boolean - returns true if the edge was created, false otherwise.

    • removeEdge

      boolean removeEdge​(T element1, T element2)
      Tries to remove an edge between two given elements. If the edge doesn't exist, it returns false.
      Parameters:
      element1 - - Element to remove the edge
      element2 - - Element to remove the edge
      Returns:
      boolean - return true if the edge was removed, false otherwise.

    • edgeTo

      boolean edgeTo​(T element1, T to)
      Checks if two elements are connected by one edge.
      Parameters:
      element1 - - Origin element
      to - - Destination element
      Returns:
      boolean - returns true if the elements are connected, false otherwise.

    • getAdjacentsOf

      Parameters:
      adjsOfT - - Element to check adjacent.
      Returns:
      Iterable of adjacents of element

      java.lang.Iterable<T> getAllElements()
      Gets all the vertices in the graph and returns it
      Returns:
      Iterable - All the vertices in the graph.
